<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05039n"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05039n">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05039n"> 39(n)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> lifelong virgin</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Being born by a special miracle without original sin, Mary was a sinless being all her lifetime. Such is the doctrine of the Catholic Church, but it was not the belief of the early Christians. They were satisfied with the idea that Mary <mark>conceived as a virgin, and remained a virgin</mark> after giving birth to Jesus. <small> G.W. Foote, <a name="TMOG" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#TMOG"><cite title="source">The Mother of God</cite></a>, (1918) 17</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
